<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: =
after-white-space;"><div>Kia ora,</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you, =
Grant, for your message proposing to convene stakeholders and provide a =
considered response. I appreciate that. =46rom what I understand, a full =
written response to my specific questions is still pending; could you =
please confirm when I will receive it, as well as the proposed meeting =
date and attendees?</div><div><br></div><div><u>Fairness &amp; =
participation</u></div><div>=46rom the ASURNZ report there were two =
assessment sessions (11 and 21 August). I wasn=E2=80=99t invited to the =
briefings or either site inspection. I appreciate this may have been an =
oversight, but it leaves me without visibility of the brief given to =
ASURNZ and what they actually saw on the day.</div><div>To balance the =
process, I kindly propose thatTower funds an independent insured-side =
assessment with me directly engaged; and I am permitted a one-on-one =
session with ASURNZ, as Grant had, so I can brief them directly and ask =
questions.</div><div>I=E2=80=99d also be grateful for the raw site notes =
and photo log from those two attendances, and for inclusion (with =
reasonable notice) in all future briefings, site visits, and =
communications.</div><div><br></div><div><u>Fire chemistry &amp; =
severity</u></div><div>=46rom the FENZ material, spa-pool =
chlorine/oxidisers were stored in the origin cupboard, dispatch added a =
HAZMAT requirement, and the incident escalated to a second alarm. In =
addition, smoke odour remains three months later. My understanding is =
that this combination raises the likelihood of corrosive/acidic residues =
and deeper smoke penetration into cavities, fixings, the roof assembly, =
and HVAC. On that basis, a visual-only approach isn=E2=80=99t =
sufficient.</div><div><br></div><div>Proposed test-led plan (please =
provide a written, insurer-funded plan and schedule showing methods, =
labs/standards, pass criteria, and dates)</div><div><ul =
class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Roof/eaves (intrusive): open selected =
eaves/roof areas; inspect underlay, battens, fixings, truss nail-plates; =
perimeter wipe/chemistry (soot/PAHs/chlorides/bromides) where odour is =
present.</li><li>Wall cavities (first-floor south/west and around the =
fireplace): remove any contaminated insulation =E2=86=92 HEPA =
clean/treat framing =E2=86=92 re-insulate =E2=86=92 re-line; wipe/swab =
sampling (framing and brick cavity); clearance criteria before =
close-up.</li><li>HVAC &amp; heating: I have heat pumps and gas heating. =
Please include internal hygiene of heat-pump heads =
(fans/coils/housings), filter change, swab testing of return paths; for =
the roof-space gas unit/any ducting, internal inspection/clean or =
replacement it contaminated; gasfitting CoC and commissioning report; =
post-clean IAQ verification and written clearance.</li><li>Electrical =
(whole installation): AS/NZS 3000 test matrix (per-circuit insulation =
resistance, polarity, earth continuity/loop, MEN, RCD trip times), =
switchboard inspection; issue EWRB CoC/ESC (RoI if mains/switchboard =
works).</li><li>Water/plumbing: system pressure/leak tests and =
disinfection/flush certificates.</li><li>Moisture &amp; corrosion: =
moisture logs prior to re-lining; corrosion screening of representative =
fasteners/plates; surface pH/chloride wipes in heat/smoke =
zones.</li><li>IAQ clearance: independent post-remediation air/surface =
clearance (soot/PAHs/halides) with chain-of-custody reporting and =
defined pass thresholds.</li></ul></div><div><br></div><div><u>Scope =
adequacy</u></div><div>=46rom the ASURNZ document, there was smoke =
migration into first-floor cavities with staining on the back of removed =
plasterboard, and roof-edge heat with deformed soffit sheeting and a =
melted gutter. The current scope appears focused on apparent damage =
(clean/smoke-seal, selective electrical checks, =E2=80=9Ctest &amp; =
recommission=E2=80=9D gas) rather than the real damage pathways =
(cavities, roof assembly, services, corrosion).</div><div>Respectfully, =
it is not only the visibly charred beams that can be compromised. =
Non-charred structural members, fixings, nail-plates, and brick/mortar =
exposed to smoke and/or acidic residues can degrade over time if not =
neutralised or replaced.</div><div>I propose the scope be revised now to =
be test-led, so that any material/component that fails objective =
criteria (chemical, structural, electrical/gas/HVAC, moisture/IAQ) is =
replaced, not sealed over.</div><div><br></div><div><u>Standard of =
reinstatement</u></div><div>My expectation is that repairs will return =
affected parts to a standard reasonably equivalent to when new =
(appearance, size, functionality, relative quality). For visible =
finishes such as brickwork, replacements should match identically in =
appearance and quality so the final result is indistinguishable and =
durable.</div><div><br></div><div><u>Building consent &amp; =
AC2213</u></div><div>ASURNZ=E2=80=99s narrative suggests no consent =
under Schedule 1/s42A. I may be mistaken, but Auckland Council=E2=80=99s =
AC2213 indicates consent is required for substantial replacement after =
fire and expects a CPEng report addressing the primary structure =
(including nail-plates/fixings at heat-affected eaves), HVAC =
removal/servicing, replacement of wet insulation, and Energy Works =
certificates for electrical/gas.</div><div>Could you =
please:</div><div><ul class=3D"MailOutline"><li>Engage a CPEng for the =
primary-structure report (including the roof/eaves zone); =
and</li><li>=E2=80=A2 Obtain Council=E2=80=99s written position for the =
final scope (consent, or a specific written exemption)? If consent is =
required, please outline LBPs/Producer Statements and =
inspections.</li></ul></div><div><br></div><div>Accommodation</div><div>I =
will wait for your proposal here. Please let me know how Tower plans to =
manage accommodation while testing, any consent/design steps, =
decontamination and reinstatement =
proceed.</div><div><br></div><div>Kindly confirm in writing (within 5 =
working days):</div><div><br></div><div>When I will receive your written =
responses and the meeting date (with =
agenda).</div><div><br></div><div>My inclusion in all future =
briefings/inspections and provision of prior =
notes/photos.</div><div><br></div><div>The testing plan (roof/eaves, =
cavities, HVAC/heat pumps &amp; gas heating, electrical, gas, water, =
moisture/corrosion, IAQ) with labs, pass criteria, and =
dates.</div><div><br></div><div>A revised scope that is test-led and =
targets as-new outcomes (not cosmetic =
sealing).</div><div><br></div><div>The Council/AC2213 path and CPEng =
engagement (consent or written exemption with =
reasons).</div><div><br></div><div>Your accommodation plan for the =
period until the home is safe and =
habitable.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for considering this. My =
aim is to keep the process fair, transparent, evidence-based, and to =
bring the house back to as-new performance and safety. I=E2=80=99m =
available this week and happy to work through the details =
together.</div><div><br></div><div>Ng=C4=81 mihi,</div><div>Raffaella =
Del Prete</div><div class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" style=3D"direction: =
ltr;"><blockquote type=3D"cite"><div>On 10 Sep 2025, at 2:03=E2=80=AFPM, =
Grant Metson &lt;Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz&gt; wrote:</div><br =
class=3D"Apple-interchange-newline"><div><span style=3D"caret-color: =
rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; =
font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; =
letter-spacing: normal; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; =
text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; =
-webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration: none; float: none; =
display: inline !important;">nd deteriorate over time, undermining both =
habitability and structural =
performance.</span></div></blockquote></div><br></body></html>=

